html2wiki: The name of the extension's entry in Special:SpecialPages
html2wiki-collection-name: If a zip file is uploaded, this is the unique name for the collection being imported.  E.g. FluxCapacitor-v1.1 such that all documents are organized around this path name at the root, and all files are tagged with this category.
html2wiki-comment: The edit history log comment if one is not provided in the web form
html2wiki-dry-run: Form label for checkbox to preview the results instead of saving
html2wiki-dry-run-heading: Heading for the actual display of 'dry-run' results
html2wiki-intro: more content at the top of [[Special:Html2Wiki]].
html2wiki-fieldset-legend: The legend of the primary fieldset in Special:Html2Wiki
html2wiki-text: Instructions on how to import HTML
html2wiki-filename:
The label for the file input element
{{Identical|Filename}}
html2wiki-not-allowed: An error message for users without permission to import HTML
html2wiki-log-name: for the Special:Log log name that appears in the drop-down on the Special:Log page
html2wiki-log-description: for the Special:Log description that appears on the Special:Log page when you filter logs on this specific log name
html2wiki_multiple_body:
Found more than one set of <body> tags in 
$1
html2wiki_uploaderror:
An error message when there is a problem with the upload. Parameters:
* $1 - the error message of the particular caught exception
html2wiki_parse-error: external library QueryPath was unable to parse the content at $1
logentry-html2wiki: Logentry on import of html pages into a wiki
